This memorandum from President Joseph R. Biden Jr. designates the Senior Director for Intelligence Programs for the National Security Council staff as the Anomalous Health Incidents (AHI) Interagency Coordinator in accordance with the National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2022. The memorandum also requests that the Secretary of State, Secretary of Defense, Attorney General, Secretary of Homeland Security, Director of National Intelligence, and Director of the Central Intelligence Agency designate senior officials to serve as AHI Agency Coordination Leads within their respective agencies. Furthermore, the memorandum directs these officials to issue updated guidance to the elements of their workforce at risk of exposure to AHI by February 25, 2022, in coordination with the AHI Interagency Coordinator. The implementation of these provisions demonstrates the Administration's commitment to the workforce and enhancing the US government's response to AHI incidents.